 have had on human culture and thought. He also offers detailed scientific descriptions of the nineteen species of owls found in North America, as well as their close relatives elsewhere. Always emphasizing the interaction of humans and owls, the author affirms by his own example the power of these birds both to beguile and to inspire.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Zoology / Ornithology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300213744423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300213744.jpg  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO